# Mail Subscription Manager - Root Context

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
Cross-platform browser extension for managing email subscriptions across Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo, etc.
Users scan their inbox once, get all subscriptions with unsubscribe links, pay $5 for lifetime unlimited access.

## GOALS
- [ ] Build cross-platform extension (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
- [ ] Implement user authentication system
- [ ] Integrate payment gateway ($5 lifetime access)
- [ ] Support multiple email providers (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo)
- [ ] Free tier: first 5 subscriptions, then paywall
- [ ] Display unsubscribe links for each subscription
- [ ] Backend API for user management and payment tracking
- [ ] Scalable, maintainable architecture

## MEMORY

### SHORT-TERM (Current Session)
- Created scalable folder structure with modular organization
- Old Chrome-only code moved to /old folder
- Setting up .windsurf context files at each module level
- Focus: Architecture and scaffolding phase

### LONG-TERM (Project History)
- Started with basic Chrome extension for Gmail
- Built working Gmail scanner using Gmail API
- OAuth2 authentication implemented for Gmail
- UI shows subscriptions but missing unsubscribe links in display
- No payment system or user accounts yet
- Chrome-only, needs cross-platform support

## ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS
1. **Modular Structure**: Separate concerns (core logic, providers, UI, backend)
2. **Provider Pattern**: Abstract email providers for multi-platform support
3. **Backend Required**: Node.js API for user accounts, payments, run tracking
4. **Storage Strategy**: Chrome Storage API (local) + Backend DB (persistent)
5. **Payment**: Stripe integration for one-time $5 payment
6. **Auth**: JWT tokens for user sessions

## PROJECT STRUCTURE
```
/src              - Frontend extension code
  /core           - Business logic (scanner, auth, storage)
  /providers      - Email provider adapters (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo)
  /ui             - User interface components
  /background     - Service worker
  /api            - Backend API client
/backend          - Server-side Node.js application
  /routes         - API endpoints
  /models         - Database models
  /middleware     - Auth, validation, etc.
/assets           - Icons, images
/old              - Legacy code (DO NOT MODIFY)
```

## WORKFLOW
1. **Check Memory**: Read this file and relevant module .windsurf files
2. **Analyze Context**: Understand current state and what needs to be done
3. **Execute Task**: Implement features following architecture rules
4. **Update Progress**: Check off completed goals, update memory
5. **Document Changes**: Record what was done in SHORT-TERM memory

